# gen193 — KB-migration of a lexical class. Coordinating conjunctions live as
# conjunction/1 facts in kb/core/lexicon.p0, and the list parsers query that class
# instead of a hardcoded C array. So the class can GROW at runtime: teaching a new
# coordinator changes parsing with NO code change. The engine is fixed; the
# lexicon learns (PRINCIPLES.md acceleration: world AND lexicon as KB).

# The built-in conjunction "and" splits a prerequisite list into separate items.
> pie requires sugar and butter
< Learned 2 prerequisites for pie.
# An UNKNOWN coordinator "p" is just another item (a bogus prerequisite).
> cake requires eggs p flour
< Learned 3 prerequisites for cake.
# Teach "p" as a conjunction — it joins the same conjunction/1 class as "and".
> use p as a conjunction
< Got it - I'll treat "p" as a conjunction now, like "and".
# Now the SAME parser splits on "p" with no code change: two items, not three.
> tart requires nuts p honey
< Learned 2 prerequisites for tart.
> how do i make tart
< To make tart: nuts, honey, then tart.
# Idempotent: teaching a known conjunction is acknowledged, not duplicated.
> use and as a conjunction
< I already treat "and" as a conjunction.
